---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Install SqueezyAgent"
  description="Draft installation notes for SqueezyAgent."
  activeDoc="/docs/install/"
  heading="Install"
  lead="Packaging is not final before v0. This page holds the future install path and current expectations."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <span class="status-pill">pre-v0 placeholder</span>
    <h2>Expected product surface</h2>
    <p>
      The first supported product surface is a local terminal UI. The current
      repository builds the CLI locally; packaged v0 release instructions will
      be published once artifacts are ready.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Target platforms</h2>
    <p>
      v0 targets macOS and Linux. The Linux release artifact is planned for
      `x86_64-unknown-linux-musl` so it can run without a glibc dependency.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Likely install notes</h2>
    <p>
      The docs should cover provider key setup, first-run indexing behavior, and
      how to run SqueezyAgent inside an existing repository once packaging is
      stable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Current CLI smoke paths</h2>
    <p>
      The CLI supports `--health` for configuration smoke checks and `--prompt`
      for a one-shot streamed response. Provider and model can be selected with
      `SQUEEZY_PROVIDER`, `SQUEEZY_MODEL`, or matching flags.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
